      <a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/k1-visa">K-1 Fiancé Visa</a> › K-2 Visa
    </div>
    <h1>K-2 Visa: Bringing Your Fiancé's Children to the U.S. (2026)</h1>
    <p class="hero-desc">The K-2 is a derivative visa that allows the unmarried children of a K-1 beneficiary to accompany or follow their parent to the United States — filed as part of the same I-129F petition.</p>
    <div class="hero-meta">
      <span class="hero-meta-item">📅 Updated May 2026</span>
      <span class="hero-meta-item">⏱ 8 min read</span>
      <span class="hero-meta-item">✅ Under 21 &amp; unmarried</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="key-stats">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="kstat">
      <div class="kstat-num">&lt;21</div>
      <div class="kstat-label">Age limit at entry</div>
    </div>
    <div class="kstat">
      <div class="kstat-num">90</div>
      <div class="kstat-label">Days to marry after K-1 entry</div>
    </div>
